# Data Model & RLS

Source: `Plans/02-data-model.md`, `Plans/01-architecture.md` §3

## Tenant isolation (non-negotiable)

- Every business table has `tenant_id`
- Every RLS policy filters by JWT `tenant_id`
- Application code never bypasses RLS except explicit `SECURITY DEFINER` admin aggregates (no row-level data leaked)
- Staff must never see cost prices or another branch's data

## Before any table/column

1. Search `02-data-model.md` and existing migrations
2. If missing → propose in `Plans/DECISIONS.md` with SQL + RLS policy + **rollback SQL**
3. Implement migration only after acceptance (or when task explicitly includes it)

## Migrations

- One concern per migration file
- Always include rollback path
- **STOP and ask** before drop/rename of columns with existing data
- Money: `NUMERIC(14,2)` · Weight: `NUMERIC(10,3)` · never float/double

## New table checklist

- [ ] `tenant_id` + index
- [ ] RLS enabled + policies for roles
- [ ] Leak test: tenant A cannot read tenant B
- [ ] `02-data-model.md` updated in same PR
